1
00:00:21,040 --> 00:00:23,240
Making such a fuss here.

2
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:24,880
Since you've let go,

3
00:00:24,880 --> 00:00:26,080
I'll be leaving now.

4
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:41,480
Y-You may rise.

5
00:00:42,160 --> 00:00:43,240
Wen Lingli.

6
00:00:43,240 --> 00:00:44,440
What's wrong?

7
00:00:44,440 --> 00:00:46,000
I sprained my ankle.

8
00:00:46,480 --> 00:00:47,480
Can't you move it?

9
00:00:47,480 --> 00:00:48,360
I can't.

10
00:00:48,480 --> 00:00:49,560
Is it swollen?

11
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:50,360
Wait a minute.

12
00:00:50,560 --> 00:00:52,200
It might be a sprained ankle.

13
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:54,330
Yin Zixi, stop right there.

14
00:00:57,120 --> 00:00:58,040
What's going on?

15
00:00:58,040 --> 00:00:59,840
Mr. Wang.

16
00:01:01,360 --> 00:01:03,560
Don't just look, help out!

17
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:06,760
I'll carry her.

18
00:01:13,039 --> 00:01:13,920
Why is this kid

19
00:01:14,039 --> 00:01:15,520
so heavy?

20
00:01:16,480 --> 00:01:17,320
Mr. Wang,

21
00:01:17,680 --> 00:01:19,200
if there's nothing else,

22
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:20,560
I'll get going.

23
00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:22,280
Wait.

24
00:01:22,840 --> 00:01:23,800
Come back.

25
00:01:25,520 --> 00:01:26,039
Zixi,

26
00:01:26,320 --> 00:01:27,760
you're usually quite quiet

27
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:29,120
in class.

28
00:01:29,360 --> 00:01:29,960
Why did you

29
00:01:29,960 --> 00:01:31,800
get into a fight with your classmate today?

30
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:32,640
This

31
00:01:33,039 --> 00:01:35,080
is a bit hard to explain.

32
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:37,560
What's so hard to explain?

33
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:38,840
Mr. Wang,

34
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,440
am I really your student?

35
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:42,360
How come I don't remember

36
00:01:42,360 --> 00:01:44,039
ever taking your class before?

37
00:01:44,039 --> 00:01:46,039
Did the fight mess with your head?

38
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:47,280
I am

39
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:48,520
your homeroom teacher,

40
00:01:48,520 --> 00:01:49,520
Mr. Wang.

41
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:53,460
Look for yourself.

42
00:01:54,039 --> 00:01:56,200
Class 1, Grade 2016, Department of Journalism.

43
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,080
Yin Zixi,

44
00:01:57,280 --> 00:01:58,000
is that you?

45
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:04,600
Prajna Paramita.

46
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:15,360
Avada Kedavra.

47
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:24,680
Diary of mysterious power,

48
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:26,440
Xiaoxi, who once made a pact with you,

49
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:27,320
commands you to

50
00:02:27,320 --> 00:02:29,200
release the seal.

51
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:32,280
Release.

52
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:33,920
Oh.

53
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:36,160
What am I doing?

54
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:40,200
My 3 million fans

55
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:41,640
are still waiting for me to log in.

56
00:02:41,640 --> 00:02:44,240
How on earth can I go back?

57
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:46,280
Where do you want to go back to?

58
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:48,520
2024, of course.

59
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:50,240
Then you need to recite

60
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:52,079
Sailor Moon's catchphrase.

61
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:56,460
The champion of love and justice.

62
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:58,600
In the name of the moon, I'll punish you!

63
00:02:58,600 --> 00:03:00,040
Goodbye, pretty girl.

64
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:02,500
Yin Zixi, where are you going?

65
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:04,320
You know me?

66
00:03:04,480 --> 00:03:05,360
Of course.

67
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:07,640
I am your best friend on planet M1703,

68
00:03:07,640 --> 00:03:09,400
Yang Qian.

69
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:10,480
Ha.

70
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:21,400
This is planet M1703.

71
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:34,400
Class 1, Journalism Department, Grade 2016.

72
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:35,560
Yin Zixi.

73
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:37,480
This is really me.

74
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:44,000
You bought so much.

75
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:45,600
I bought it with my mom.

76
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:47,520
She recently got obsessed with watching live streams.

77
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:49,040
A man selling lipsticks.

78
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:50,480
Oh my god, buy it.

79
00:03:50,720 --> 00:03:52,250
You watch live streams too?

80
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:55,960
At least I have 3 million followers.

81
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,700
Three million followers?

82
00:03:58,920 --> 00:03:59,800
I remember.

83
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:02,200
He seems to only have tens of thousands of followers.

84
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:03,520
That's now.

85
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:06,200
He suddenly reached three million followers.

86
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:08,200
Gaining followers isn't that easy.

87
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:09,440
From now on...

88
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:10,920
If it were me...

89
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:14,400
Is this my destiny?

90
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,680
The top livestreamer,

91
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:16,640
Yin Zixi.

92
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:26,920
I need to turn over a new leaf

93
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:29,000
and start fresh.

94
00:04:41,159 --> 00:04:43,159
Please enjoy.

95
00:04:43,159 --> 00:04:45,360
Hey, Brother Liang Chen,

96
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:46,920
is your selection confirmed this time?

97
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:47,840
Yes.

98
00:04:47,840 --> 00:04:49,800
But what's going on with your side?

99
00:04:50,280 --> 00:04:52,960
I might have gone a bit too far this time.

100
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:54,120
Too far?

101
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,520
It's simply outrageous.

102
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:56,960
In the entire competition,

103
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:58,690
you are actually the only girl.

104
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,000
Well, I just

105
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:00,960
approached those girls

106
00:05:00,960 --> 00:05:02,360
for a little chat, that's all.

107
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:03,040
Yeah.

108
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:05,240
But the other girls are all too scared to participate.

109
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:06,000
What?

110
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,760
Is it my fault that they are cowards?

111
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:08,640
No.

112
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:11,520
Oh, I have a good idea.

113
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:14,440
We can find some

114
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:16,040
plain girls to participate.

115
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,480
It won't affect your chances,

116
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:19,740
and the teacher won't suspect anything.

117
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:21,240
Plain?

118
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:23,660
I have someone in mind.

119
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:24,480
Who?

120
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:26,240
The first one,

121
00:05:26,280 --> 00:05:28,040
Yin Zixi.

122
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:31,760
Do you want to keep your current length

123
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:33,440
or try a shorter style?

124
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:34,940
I want the current length.

125
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:36,400
How about this.

126
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:37,480
A high ponytail makes you look more elegant.

127
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:38,240
This Yin Zixi

128
00:05:38,280 --> 00:05:39,080
is in our class.

129
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:41,520
The one who always wears her high school uniform

130
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:42,600
and looks so tacky.

131
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:44,159
She gave me a hard time before,

132
00:05:44,159 --> 00:05:47,560
so it's a good chance to let her make a fool of herself on stage.

133
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:49,520
Done writing.

134
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:52,360
Can they all come?

135
00:05:53,960 --> 00:05:54,840
When I handle things,

136
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:56,170
you don't need to worry.

137
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:57,920
Go ahead.

138
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:01,040
Keep up the good work.

139
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:01,770
I'm leaving.

140
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:08,200
Yang Qian.

141
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:11,800
Huh? Where is everyone?

142
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,000
I went home today.

143
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:21,680
There's an invitation for you on the desk.

144
00:06:26,760 --> 00:06:28,200
Dear Yin Zixi,

145
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:29,520
Your temperament and image

146
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:32,240
have impressed the Xihai University Endorsement Preparatory Committee.

147
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:32,960
We hereby invite you

148
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:34,600
to participate in tomorrow's selection event.

149
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:35,560
What the hell?

150
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:38,120
I'm not participating.

151
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:44,600
What's wrong with this diary again?

152
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:49,640
The preparatory committee sent me an invitation.

153
00:06:49,640 --> 00:06:51,920
I don't know how they found me,

154
00:06:52,159 --> 00:06:54,920
but I decided to give it a try.

155
00:06:56,880 --> 00:06:58,760
What's going on?

156
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:02,680
Why are there so few people?

157
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:06,120
Hello.

158
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:08,600
Hi beautiful,

159
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:09,560
who are you?

160
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:11,080
I'm Yin Zixi.

161
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:15,680
The college entrance exam is like thousands of troops

162
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:16,880
crossing a single-log bridge.

163
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:17,840
We worked so hard

164
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:19,000
to get into college.

165
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:21,840
I didn't expect her to join too.

166
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:24,060
Finally, someone decent.

167
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:24,680
Mr. Wang,

168
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:26,240
is this your student?

169
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:29,410
It's a pity the speech was average.

170
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:31,680
And the lines weren't well-memorized.

171
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:34,360
It is a bit of a shame.

172
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:36,080
From the first day of college,

173
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:38,640
students must set clear goals.

174
00:07:39,159 --> 00:07:40,640
I hope later on stage,

175
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:42,040
this diary

176
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:43,700
won't cause any more trouble.

177
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:48,000
Guided by the right goals,

178
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,159
we can start a brand new voyage.

179
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:52,080
That concludes my speech.

180
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:53,409
Thank you, professors.

181
00:07:59,120 --> 00:07:59,640
Next.

182
00:07:59,640 --> 00:08:00,400
Yin Zixi.

183
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:20,960
Hello, professors.

184
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:23,280
I am from the 2016 Journalism Class 1,

185
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:24,120
Yin Zixi.

186
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,920
So you are Yin Zixi.

187
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,240
Please begin.

188
00:08:44,039 --> 00:08:46,400
Am I going to be dragged on stage

189
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:48,060
to make a fool of myself again?

190
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:02,640
For the campus ambassador selection,

191
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:03,520
winners will receive

192
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:05,040
a school-sponsored startup fund

193
00:09:05,040 --> 00:09:07,370
and on-campus entrepreneurial support.

194
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:24,000
Returning to campus,

195
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:25,200
I can't help but

196
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:25,800
think about

197
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:27,640
my days as a student.

198
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:30,280
I wonder if you've ever thought about

199
00:09:30,280 --> 00:09:32,400
what you'll be like in seven years.

200
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:33,800
Where will you be?

201
00:09:33,920 --> 00:09:35,280
What will you be doing?

202
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:36,840
Sigh.

203
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:39,600
This is a headache.

204
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:40,800
Ah.

205
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:43,760
Wen Lingli's is over.

206
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:44,560
It's over.

207
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:46,480
Boss, why are you here?

208
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:49,600
We cannot be certain of

209
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:50,720
our future.

210
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:51,850
The one on the stage.

211
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:53,280
Who is it?

212
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:55,560
Um, Yin Zixi.

213
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:57,740
Wen Lingli has finally met her match.

214
00:09:59,040 --> 00:10:00,000
But precisely because

215
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,520
there are so many uncertainties,

216
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:02,440
all of this

217
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:04,680
is waiting for us to figure out.

218
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:17,240
Assistant Casting Director Xi Chongjingü

219
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:19,120
Props Assistant Li Kunxiao

220
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:21,080
Transport Yi Mingle

221
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:23,040
Yitong
